DURBAN - The body of a female that was washed away during heavy rains has been recovered this morning in Amoiti In KwaZulu-Natal.

 

 The heavy rain that struck Durban on Sunday caused severe damage in townships and rural areas, with homes and infrastructure damaged. Local security company, 
 Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa), discovered the body, said that they received a call from councillors in the area today requesting air support.

 

 The body of a male and a child was recovered earlier this week. 
 Rusa spokesperson Prem Balram said that after a briefing, the pilot flew along the river while search and rescue members used a rubber dinghy & a dog to search the water. 

 

 
  
  
   Reaction Unit South Africa have during a search of a body of a woman that drowned on Sunday. Image: Supplied. 
  
 

 “Police members recovered the body a short while later near a bridge. The body was covered with reeds and was sniffed out by the rescue dog,” said Balram.

 

 Barlam said, “It is believed that the family drowned after their house collapsed during the heavy rain.”

 

 The KZN Department of co-operative governance and traditional affairs (Cogta) MEC Nomusa Dube-Ncube, together with eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede, visited the affected areas earlier this week.

 

 
  
  
